<LegalPage
  title="Accessibility Statement"
  subtitle="Our commitment to making this website usable for everyone."
  description="Accessibility Statement for Chagrin Electronic Recycling — our commitment to WCAG 2.1 AA and how to request accommodations."
  lastUpdated="June 26, 2026"
>
  <p>
    Chagrin Electronic Recycling ("CER") is committed to ensuring that our website and services
    are accessible to people with disabilities. We want everyone in our community to be able to
    learn about our recycling services and reach us easily, regardless of ability or the
    technology they use.
  </p>

  <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
  <p>
    We strive to conform to the
    <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/standards-guidelines/wcag/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
      Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1, Level AA
    </a>.
    These internationally recognized guidelines help make web content more accessible to people
    with a wide range of disabilities, including visual, hearing, cognitive, and motor
    impairments. We also work toward consistency with the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA).
  </p>

  <h2>Measures We Take</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Using semantic, structured HTML so content works well with assistive technologies.</li>
    <li>Providing descriptive text alternatives for meaningful images and icons.</li>
    <li>Maintaining readable color contrast and legible text sizing.</li>
    <li>Ensuring the site can be navigated with a keyboard, including a "skip to content" link.</li>
    <li>Labeling form fields clearly and providing visible focus indicators.</li>
    <li>Designing a responsive layout that adapts to different devices and screen sizes.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Ongoing Effort</h2>
  <p>
    Accessibility is an ongoing process, not a one-time project. We regularly review the Site and
    work to improve the experience for all users. Some content provided by third parties (such as
    embedded maps or social media feeds) may not be fully under our control, but we make
    reasonable efforts to choose accessible solutions and provide alternatives where practical.
  </p>

  <h2>Need Help or Found a Problem?</h2>
  <p>
    If you have difficulty using any part of this website, or if you need information or services
    provided in a different format, we want to help. Please contact us and we will do our best to
    provide the information, service, or accommodation you need through an alternative method.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Chagrin Electronic Recycling</strong><br />
    10140 Gottschalk Pkwy, Chagrin Falls, OH 44022<br />
    Phone: <a href="tel:+14406019166">(440) 601-9166</a><br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:Chagrin-E-Recycling@scarce-resources.com">Chagrin-E-Recycling@scarce-resources.com</a>
  </p>
  <p>
    When you contact us, please describe the issue you ran into and the page or feature involved,
    so we can address it as quickly as possible. We welcome your feedback and suggestions for how
    we can make our website more accessible.
  </p>
</LegalPage>
